<div  lang="en"><header class="entry-header" nodeIndex="162">
<div class="intro-text" nodeIndex="165">
<p nodeIndex="166"><strong nodeIndex="591"><em nodeIndex="592">Instant Pot Chicken Curry</em></strong> <em nodeIndex="593">is a&nbsp;comforting dish that is full of flavour. It is easy to make from pantry staples and is suitable for Paleo, Keto, Low Carb&nbsp;and Gluten-Free diets. Post includes Weight Watchers points.</em></p>
</div>
</header><div class="entry-content" itemprop="text" nodeIndex="167"><div id="RIL_IMG_1" class="RIL_IMG"></div>
<div class="mailmunch-forms-before-post" nodeIndex="178"></div>
<p nodeIndex="179">Let&rsquo;s make some curry today, folks. Not just any curry &ndash; <strong nodeIndex="595">EASY, creamy curry that is full of flavour and packed with protein</strong>. It&rsquo;s the kind of simple Indian Chicken curry that is so easy to make and so lovely that you&rsquo;ll find yourself saying &lsquo;I need to make this every day.&rsquo; No need to order a takeaway when you can whip up a simple homemade curry yourself.</p>
<p nodeIndex="180">I make curry quite often &ndash; <a href="https://recipesfromapantry.com/egg-curry/" nodeIndex="596">egg curry</a>, <a href="https://recipesfromapantry.com/15-min-thai-red-prawn-curry/" nodeIndex="597">prawn curry</a>, &nbsp;<a href="https://recipesfromapantry.com/tanzanian-inspired-mushroom-curry-vegan/" nodeIndex="598">mushroom curry</a> &ndash; but I admit this Instant Pot Chicken Curry recipe might be my favourite. Why? Well&hellip;.</p>
<h2 nodeIndex="181">Why You&rsquo;ll Love Instant Pot Chicken Curry</h2>
<p nodeIndex="182"><strong nodeIndex="599">It is an Instant Pot curry.</strong> I am convinced that everything is easier in the Instant Pot. With a few simple steps, you&rsquo;ll have this curry recipe whipped up in no time at all.</p>
<p nodeIndex="183"><strong nodeIndex="600">It is a one-pot recipe.</strong> See above about using the Instant Pot. Everything you need for this recipe will be done in the Instant Pot inner pot&hellip; why dirty multiple dishes when you can do it all in one??</p>
<div id="RIL_IMG_2" class="RIL_IMG"></div>
<p nodeIndex="185"><strong nodeIndex="603">It uses pantry staples.</strong> Nothing difficult to find in this recipe, folks.</p>
<p nodeIndex="186"><strong nodeIndex="604">Make a slow cooker version.</strong> You can make slow cooker Indian chicken curry if you prefer. I show you how to below.</p>
<p nodeIndex="187"><strong nodeIndex="605">It is suitable for a variety of diets.</strong> Paleo, Whole 30 and Gluten-Free folks will all be happy with this recipe. And folks on Weight Watchers will be happy with the points count on this recipe, too.</p>
<p nodeIndex="188"><strong nodeIndex="606">It has magical powers.</strong> Maaaaybe that is taking it too far, but with comforting spices like cinnamon, cloves, curry and garam masala, plus garlic and ginger, there is a whole lot of goodness in this dish.</p>
<h2 nodeIndex="189"><span nodeIndex="607">Instant Pot Chicken Curry Tools</span></h2>
<div class="affiliate-box-blue" nodeIndex="190">
<p nodeIndex="191"><strong nodeIndex="608">KITCHEN TOOLS, UTENSILS &amp; APPLIANCES&nbsp; NEEDED</strong></p>
<p nodeIndex="192"><em nodeIndex="609">This post contains affiliate links. For more information, check out my <a href="https://recipesfromapantry.com/privacy-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" nodeIndex="610">disclosure</a>.</em></p>
<p nodeIndex="193">Here are some of the items you will need to make this recipe.</p>
</div>
<h2 nodeIndex="206">How to Make Instant Pot Chicken Curry</h2>
<p nodeIndex="207">Ready to make some chicken curry in Instant Pot?? Gather your ingredients and let me show you how&hellip;</p>
<p nodeIndex="208"><strong nodeIndex="611">Step 1.</strong> In saut&eacute; mode, add the oil to the inner pot of the Instant Pot. Wait till hot, then add the onion, cinnamon stick and cloves and saut&eacute; for 5-7 mins. You can add 2 tbsp of water to avoid burning the onion.</p>
<div id="RIL_IMG_3" class="RIL_IMG"></div>
<p nodeIndex="210"><strong nodeIndex="614">Step 2.</strong> Add the&nbsp;chicken&nbsp;pieces and brown them for a couple of mins.</p>
<div id="RIL_IMG_4" class="RIL_IMG"></div>
<p nodeIndex="212"><strong nodeIndex="617">Step 3.</strong> Switch off the saut&eacute; mode and add the garlic ginger,&nbsp;curry&nbsp;powder, garam masala, chopped tomatoes, the water bit of the coconut milk, salt and chilli (if using) and mix.</p>
<div id="RIL_IMG_5" class="RIL_IMG"></div>
<p nodeIndex="214"><strong nodeIndex="620">Step 4.</strong> Cover your Instant Pot and set the valve to the SEALING position.</p>
<p nodeIndex="215"><strong nodeIndex="621">Step 5.</strong> Select the manual setting, make sure the pressure is set to high and set the timer to 5 mins.</p>
<p nodeIndex="216"><strong nodeIndex="622">Step 6.</strong> Cook till done then let the steam release naturally before opening.</p>
<div id="RIL_IMG_6" class="RIL_IMG"></div>
<div class="mailmunch-forms-in-post-middle" nodeIndex="218"></div>
<p nodeIndex="219"><strong nodeIndex="625">Step 7.</strong> Switch to saut&eacute; mode, stir in the coconut cream and saut&eacute; for 2 mins.</p>
<p nodeIndex="220"><strong nodeIndex="626">Step 8.</strong> Switch off and adjust seasoning, remove the cinnamon stick and serve.</p>
<div id="RIL_IMG_7" class="RIL_IMG"></div>
<h2 nodeIndex="222">Tips for Making Instant Pot Chicken Curry</h2>
<ul nodeIndex="224"><li nodeIndex="223">Use olive oil or coconut oil if you want the recipe to be Paleo- and Whole 30-compliant.</li>
<li nodeIndex="225">Weight Watchers followers should use a calorie-controlled cooking spray instead of the oil to cut down on points.</li>
<li nodeIndex="226">Use full-fat tinned coconut milk, not coconut milk from a carton. You will need to use the divided (cream/water) coconut milk to achieve the ideal curry consistency.</li>
</ul><h2 nodeIndex="227">&nbsp;Slow Cooker Indian Chicken Curry</h2>
<p nodeIndex="228">Fancy making a&nbsp;slow cooker Indian chicken curry instead?&nbsp;Well, here is how to do so.</p>
<p nodeIndex="229"><strong nodeIndex="629">Step 1.</strong> Saut&eacute; the onion, cinnamon stick and cloves in a frying pan for 5-7 mins. You can add 2 tbsp of water to avoid burning the onion.</p>
<p nodeIndex="230"><strong nodeIndex="630">Step 2.</strong> Add the&nbsp;chicken&nbsp;pieces and brown them for a couple of mins.</p>
<p nodeIndex="231"><strong nodeIndex="631">Step 3.</strong> Mix in the garlic ginger,&nbsp;curry&nbsp;powder, garam masala, chopped tomatoes, the water bit of the coconut milk, salt and chilli (if using) and switch of the heat.</p>
<p nodeIndex="232"><strong nodeIndex="632">Step 4.</strong> Transfer the chicken curry mix into your <a href="https://amzn.to/2KYT0De" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" nodeIndex="633">slow cooker</a> and cook on low for 5-6 hrs or on high for 3-4 hrs.</p>
<p nodeIndex="233"><strong nodeIndex="634">Step 5.</strong> When done stir in the coconut cream, adjust season, let cook for a few more mins until warmed through and serve.</p>
<div id="RIL_IMG_8" class="RIL_IMG"></div>
<h2 nodeIndex="235">Creamy Chicken Curry Soup</h2>
<p nodeIndex="236">You can easily make this a&nbsp;creamy chicken curry soup. Just add an extra 240ml (1 cup) to 480ml (2 cups) of chicken stock when cooking. Add the smaller amount if you prefer a thicker soup.</p>
<h2 nodeIndex="237">What to Serve with this easy Instant Pot Chicken Curry</h2>
<p nodeIndex="238">If not Paleo or Whole 30, you can make <a href="https://recipesfromapantry.com/instant-pot-rice/" nodeIndex="637">Instant Pot rice</a> to serve alongside this easy Instant Pot curry recipe, or you can serve with naan or chapatti bread. If Paleo or Whole 30, you can make <a href="https://recipesfromapantry.com/cauliflower-rice/" nodeIndex="638">cauliflower rice</a> for a gluten-free and grain-free &lsquo;rice.&rsquo;</p>
<h2 nodeIndex="239">Weight Watchers Points in Instant Pot Chicken Curry</h2>
<p nodeIndex="240">If you replace the 2 tbsp oil used for frying with a calorie-controlled cooking spray, there are:</p>
<ul nodeIndex="242"><li nodeIndex="241"><strong nodeIndex="639">7 Freestyle points&nbsp;</strong>per serving</li>
<li nodeIndex="243"><strong nodeIndex="640">3 PointsPlus points&nbsp;</strong>per serving</li>
</ul><h2 nodeIndex="244">Want More Flavourful Instant Pot Chicken Recipes?</h2>
